## 1. General Principles

- **Language:** ALL code, comments, commit messages, variable names, and documentation within the codebase MUST be written in **English**. No exceptions.
- **Clarity over brevity:** Names must be self-documenting. A longer descriptive name is always preferred over a short ambiguous abbreviation.
- **Domain-driven vocabulary:** Use terminology from the crypto trading domain consistently. Never invent synonyms. Use the canonical terms: `strategy`, `bot_instance`, `backtest`, `candle`, `session`, `lifecycle_variable`, `unit_cost`, `pnl`, `equity`, `fill_price`, `realized_pnl`, `unrealized_pnl`, `drawdown`, `symbol`, `timeframe`, `leverage`, `margin`.
- **No magic values:** Every status string, threshold, or business constant must be defined as a typed constant or enum — never hardcoded inline. Examples: bot statuses (`Running`, `Stopped`, `Error`), strategy statuses (`Draft`, `Valid`, `Archived`), trade sides (`Long`, `Short`).

---

## 2. Backend Naming Conventions (Go)

### 2.1 Packages

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Package name | `lowercase`, single word, no underscores | `handler`, `logic`, `repository`, `domain`, `engine` |
| Internal packages | Under `internal/` — unexportable by design | `internal/logic`, `internal/handler` |
| Shared utilities | Under `pkg/` — importable by external consumers | `pkg/crypto`, `pkg/response` |

### 2.2 Types & Structs

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Exported struct | `PascalCase`, noun, singular | `BotInstance`, `TradeHistory`, `StrategyVersion` |
| Unexported struct | `camelCase` | `candleBuffer`, `sessionContext` |
| Interface | `PascalCase`, behavior-descriptive; single-method interfaces use `-er` suffix | `StrategyRepository`, `OrderExecutor`, `TokenRefresher` |
| Interface file | Collected in `interfaces.go` within the `repository` package | — |

### 2.3 Functions & Methods

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Exported function | `PascalCase`, verb-first | `CreateBotInstance()`, `CalculateRSI()`, `EncryptSecretKey()` |
| Unexported function | `camelCase`, verb-first | `validateOrderParams()`, `buildCandleQuery()` |
| Constructor | `New` + type name | `NewBotManager()`, `NewBacktestSimulator()` |
| Handler method | HTTP verb context implied; name describes the action | `Login()`, `ListStrategies()`, `StopBot()` |
| Logic layer method | Business-action oriented | `ExecuteBacktest()`, `StartBotInstance()`, `SyncMarketData()` |
| Repository method | CRUD-verb + entity | `CreateUser()`, `FindBotByID()`, `UpdateTotalPnL()`, `DeleteStrategy()` |

### 2.4 Variables & Constants

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Exported constant | `PascalCase` | `MaxLoginAttempts`, `LockoutDurationMinutes`, `DefaultUnitCostLimit` |
| Unexported constant | `camelCase` | `defaultPageSize`, `heartbeatInterval` |
| Local variable | `camelCase`, short but descriptive | `botID`, `fillPrice`, `totalPnL` |
| Loop variable | Single letter only for trivial loops | `i`, `j`, `k` |
| Error variable | Always `err`; wrap with `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)` | — |
| Context | Always `ctx` as first parameter | `func (s *BotLogic) Start(ctx context.Context, ...)` |

### 2.5 Goroutine & Channel Naming

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Channel variable | Suffix `Ch` or describe the payload | `candleCh`, `orderResultCh`, `stopSignal` |
| Goroutine launcher | Prefix `go` in the wrapping function name, or describe the worker | `runBotWorker()`, `listenKlineStream()` |

