## 3. Frontend Naming Conventions (TypeScript / React)

### 3.1 Files & Directories

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| React component file | `kebab-case.tsx` | `candle-chart.tsx`, `bot-tab.tsx`, `blockly-workspace.tsx` |
| Utility / lib file | `kebab-case.ts` | `auth.ts`, `utils.ts` |
| Type definition file | `kebab-case.ts` under `types/` | `index.ts`, `trading.ts` |
| Directory | `kebab-case` | `components/trading/`, `components/editor/` |
| Next.js route group | Parenthesized `kebab-case` | `(dashboard)/`, `login/` |

### 3.2 Components

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Component name | `PascalCase`, noun-descriptive | `CandleChart`, `MarketWatch`, `BacktestTab`, `SettingsDialog` |
| Component props type | Component name + `Props` | `CandleChartProps`, `BotTabProps` |
| Custom hook | `use` prefix + `camelCase` | `useWebSocket`, `useMarketTicker`, `useBotLogs` |
| Context | `PascalCase` + `Context` / `Provider` | `AuthContext`, `AuthProvider` |

### 3.3 Variables & Functions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Local variable | `camelCase` | `botInstance`, `currentSymbol`, `equityCurve` |
| Boolean variable | `is` / `has` / `should` prefix | `isLoading`, `hasOpenPosition`, `shouldReconnect` |
| Constant (module-level) | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `MAX_RECONNECT_DELAY_MS`, `WS_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL` |
| Event handler | `handle` + event noun | `handleLogin`, `handleStartBot`, `handleSymbolChange` |
| Callback prop | `on` + event noun | `onLogin`, `onBotStarted`, `onSymbolChange` |
| Fetcher / API call | `fetch` / `create` / `update` / `delete` + entity | `fetchStrategies()`, `createBotInstance()`, `deleteApiKey()` |

### 3.4 TypeScript Types & Interfaces

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Interface / Type | `PascalCase`, no `I` prefix | `BotInstance`, `TradeRecord`, `CandleData` |
| Enum | `PascalCase` name, `PascalCase` members | `BotStatus.Running`, `OrderSide.Long` |
| Generic type param | Single uppercase letter or short descriptor | `T`, `TData`, `TResponse` |
| Union type for statuses | String literal union | `type BotStatus = "Running" \| "Stopped" \| "Error"` |

