## 4. Database Naming Conventions (PostgreSQL)

### 4.1 Tables & Columns

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Table name | `snake_case`, plural | `bot_instances`, `strategy_versions`, `candles_data` |
| Column name | `snake_case` | `user_id`, `fill_price`, `secret_key_encrypted` |
| Primary key | Always `id` | `id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()` |
| Foreign key column | Referenced table (singular) + `_id` | `user_id`, `bot_id`, `strategy_version_id` |
| Timestamp columns | `created_at`, `updated_at`, `executed_at` — always `TIMESTAMPTZ` | — |
| Boolean column | `is_` prefix | `is_closed` |
| Status column | Named `status`, type `VARCHAR(20)`, with a documented set of allowed values | `status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Draft'` |

### 4.2 Constraints & Indexes

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Primary key | Implicit via `PRIMARY KEY` | — |
| Foreign key constraint | `fk_<parent>_<child>` | `fk_user_api`, `fk_bot_trade` |
| Unique constraint | `uk_<descriptive>` | `uk_strategy_version`, `uk_symbol_interval_opentime` |
| Index | `idx_<table>_<columns>` | `idx_candles_symbol_interval_time`, `idx_bot_status` |

---

## 5. API & WebSocket Naming Conventions

### 5.1 REST API

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Base path | `/api/v1/` | — |
| Resource path | `kebab-case`, plural nouns | `/strategies`, `/api-keys`, `/bot-instances` |
| Action sub-path | Verb for non-CRUD actions | `/auth/login`, `/auth/logout`, `/auth/refresh` |
| Query params | `snake_case` | `?bot_id=...&page_size=20` |
| JSON request body | `snake_case` keys | `{ "api_key": "...", "secret_key": "..." }` |
| JSON response body | `snake_case` keys | `{ "total_pnl": 0.5, "created_at": "..." }` |
| Error response code | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `INVALID_CREDENTIALS`, `ACCOUNT_LOCKED`, `UNIT_COST_EXCEEDED` |

### 5.2 WebSocket

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Channel name | `snake_case` | `market_ticker`, `bot_logs`, `position_update` |
| Event name | `snake_case` | `subscribed`, `unsubscribed`, `ping`, `pong` |
| Action field | `snake_case` verb | `subscribe`, `unsubscribe` |
| Param keys | `snake_case` | `{ "symbol": "BTCUSDT", "bot_id": "..." }` |

