## 8. File & Directory Naming

### 8.1 Backend (Go)

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Go source file | `snake_case.go` | `auth_handler.go`, `bot_logic.go`, `candle_repo.go` |
| Test file | `snake_case_test.go` | `auth_logic_test.go`, `order_matcher_test.go` |
| Domain entity file | Singular entity name | `user.go`, `bot_instance.go`, `strategy_version.go` |
| Package directory | Single `lowercase` word | `handler/`, `logic/`, `repository/`, `domain/` |
| Engine sub-package | Descriptive lowercase | `engine/blockly/`, `engine/backtest/`, `engine/bot/` |

### 8.2 Frontend (TypeScript / Next.js)

| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Component file | `kebab-case.tsx` | `candle-chart.tsx`, `settings-dialog.tsx` |
| Utility file | `kebab-case.ts` | `utils.ts`, `auth.ts` |
| Route directory | `kebab-case` or Next.js group `(group-name)` | `(dashboard)/`, `editor/`, `trading/` |
| Layout file | `layout.tsx` (Next.js convention) | — |
| Page file | `page.tsx` (Next.js convention) | — |
| Type file | `kebab-case.ts` under `types/` | `types/index.ts` |

---

## Summary Checklist

Before submitting any code, verify:

- [ ] All names follow the casing convention for their layer (Go/TS/SQL).
- [ ] All financial variables use the mandatory suffix (`_price`, `_amount`, `_pnl`, `_fee`, `_quantity`, `_rate`, `_balance`, `_capital`, `_volume`).
- [ ] All status values are defined as typed constants — no raw strings.
- [ ] All comments are in English.
- [ ] No comment restates what the code syntax already shows — every comment explains "why".
- [ ] Exported Go types and functions have GoDoc comments.
- [ ] Complex React components and custom hooks have JSDoc comments.
- [ ] Security-sensitive code blocks have explicit comments referencing the NFR code.
- [ ] `DECIMAL(18,8)` is used for all financial columns — no `FLOAT` or `DOUBLE`.
- [ ] `float64` is never used for financial arithmetic in Go — use `decimal.Decimal` or `math/big`.
